The best value is definitely the pre-made burgers as it costs more to customize your burger even if you choose the exact same ingredients. The burger is "fancy" and the prices are therefore higher. The portion size is good, not humongous - it's filling and you probably won't leave hungry, especially if you get fries. Which I suggest - get the fries.

The bartender was very friendly, as were the other staff members.

Staff was decent. The burgers are typically overpriced because of the area it is in. Happy hour beers are about 6.50 a piece. More of a craft beer menu. The burgers were on average between $13-$16. While delicious, they sure weren't worth that kind of money also considering it didn't come with a side and the burger was about the size of a big mac. Atleast the people working here are friendly.

My black Iron burger was cooked to perfection and topped off with condiments that compliment it in the best way. The side of truffle fries made a great combo as well. HOWEVER, everything was salted to hell and the exceptional flavor was unfortunately buried underneath.

This new joint on Flatbush Ave is not just about the burgers! Friendly attentive service. Counter or table seating. Currently a generous happy hour until 9pm. This is the 3rd outpost in NYC. Chipotle BBQ wings were excellent and The Masterpiece Burger tasty and filling. One starter, two burgers and a side of fries were more than enough for two people.
Food was good. Well seasoned, medium burger came more medium rare but not bad. Nice, friendly service. More expensive than 67 burger that use to be there.
Best burger in the city! Love this place and this new location. No wonder Zagat rated it number one burger in NYC!!!

Finally! Been waiting for this location to open up ever since I got word back in April. I'm glad to note this is now one of my preferred burger 🍔 locations in the neighborhood. It really is hard to find good burgers around here and this place finally nailed it! Great location close to the Barclay's.  We had the Black Iron Burger (pic not shown), Iberico and The Masterpiece. While all three were tasty my favorite was the Iberico. That ham reminded me of like a tasty prosciutto. The saltiness was perfect 👌 on it with the fried egg and Arugula. The Black Iron Burger sauce reminded me a little bit of a Big Mac, however that's really were the comparison ends. Very tasty sauce and even though there is horse radish in it and the cheese, we never could actually taste that, or the expected spice kick it would bring. It all blended well together.  I didn't have bad service like a few had noted. Wasn't the fastest, but also not slow. Since they JUST opened this week I also didn't expect them to fully have their rhythm going and will just get better over time. People need to just chill out and enjoy the food. Shake Shack for quick tasty burgers and now Black Iron Burger for the next level. Skip the other places and come here, folks!
I heard of it and I had to go,  totally true!! Best burguers of NYC! I'll be back for sure

New great location for BIB in the up&coming Brooklyn hood. In the heart of Flatbush Ave.  Their burgers are the best in town by far. I tried the new grilled red peppers with egg available in this location.

Waited 10 minutes for a bottled soda. Did they have to make the soda from scratch? As I was typing this (as nosy as they are, the waitress attempts to look at my phone), they tell me they don't have it. That took ten minutes. Another 5 minutes, to make a float. That's 2 scoops (they gave me one), of ice cream, and soda in a glass. Glad I didn't order a burger. Would've been here until Thanksgiving. No more than 6 people when I walked in. Who do they have working back there? Cecil the Turtle?
Very tasty burgers and fries. Both could have been cooked a little more but still very good. Friendly nice and new spot. We'll be back for sure.
